        <headline>Flash Flood Warning issued July 4 at 3:44AM CDT until July 4 at 4:30AM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 338 AM CDT, Local Law Enforcement reported flash flooding along
US 87 near FM2105, FM2288, in Carlsbad, and in Grape Creek where
they currently have water rescues ongoing for people in flooded
cars. Expect storm totals of 10 to 12 inches mainly between San
Angelo and Grape Creek. Also, expect fast and swifting flowing water
which is very dangerous. Flash flooding is currently ongoing.

HAZARD...Life threatening flash flooding. Thunderstorms producing
flash flooding.

SOURCE...Law enforcement reported.

IMPACT...Life threatening flash flooding of creeks and streams,
urban areas, highways, streets and underpasses.

Some locations that will experience flash flooding include...
San Angelo, Grape Creek, Goodfellow Air Force Base and Carlsbad.
</description>
        <instruction>Turn around, don't drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood
deaths occur in vehicles.

Be especially cautious at night when it is harder to recognize the
dangers of flooding.

Be aware of your surroundings and do not drive on flooded roads.</instruction>
